@node "WhatIs" "What Is CutIT?"
@next "Require"
@prev "Main"


CutIT is small and fast utility that will split AmiNet INDEX file, to many
'smaller' parts. What does it mean?

It will take each 'theme' and 'subtheme', and will create files with names
like...

biz_dbase biz_demo biz_dopus biz_misc

...and will place them in desired directory.

It is usefull for people with less RAM, and less nerves (when You try to
search for string "source" i.e., and You find it in every 30th line ;).

Also, if You know WHERE and WHAT to search for, it will be a piece of cake
to find it...

I decided to make this, because I had a chance to use similar utility that
splitted my INDEX file for 25 minutes(!?) on A4000/040.


@{"NEXT" link "Require" 0}
@endnode

@node "Require" "Requirements"
@prev "Main"


- An Amiga
- Kickstart 3.X
- AmiNet INDEX file
- Some MBs on hard disk to place result files in

CutIT was tested on A4000/040 with OS3.0. Haven't tested it on OS2.X yet,
but I think it will work fine.


@{"NEXT" link "Install" 0}
@endnode

