@node "Usage" "Usage"
@prev "Install"


Syntax is:

CutIT <index file> <directory where you want to place result files>

In example:

6.Temp:SC/CutIT> CutIT dh1:temp/index dh2:Index

In this case, INDEX file is located in dh1:temp, and result files will be
created in dh2:Index directory.

Of course, You can do everything in RAM:, it will be a bit faster!

Here are some speed results:

--[ Caches ON ]--

Index	ResultDir

Ram:	Ram:		16.30 sec
dh1:	Ram:		18.74 sec
dh1:	dh2:		23.16 sec

--[ Caches OFF ]--

Index	ResultDir

Ram:	Ram:		92.40 sec
dh1:	ram:		96.62 sec
dh1:	dh2:		96.65 sec

(NOTE: It was tested on A4000/040-25MHz & 18Mb RAM)


